Class RegExHashMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentHashMap<K,V>
        • RegExHashMap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - : Key of the map item.
    V - : Value of the map item.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentMap<K,V>, java.util.Map<K,V>

    public class RegExHashMap<K,V>
extends java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentHashMap<K,V>
    This class is an extended version of Java HashMap and includes pattern-value lists which are used to evaluate regular expression values. If given item is a regular expression, it is saved in regexp lists. If requested item matches with a regular expression, its value is get from regexp lists.
    Author:
    cb
